[2026-03-13T17:40:25Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EN2btuzFKJQ3rtujmZfjq7","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary: Project Runs URL Pattern (`runs?project=[project_path]`)\n\nBased on my thorough search of the codebase, here's a complete analysis of where and how the `runs?project` URL pattern is defined and used:\n\n### 1. **HTTP Route Definition**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 146-152)\n\n```go\nh.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /{$}\", h.handleProjectOverview)\nh.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /projects/{name}/runs\", h.handleProjectRuns)\nh.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /runs\", h.handleRunsList)\nh.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs\", h.handleAPIRuns)\n```\n\nThe web server uses Go 1.22+ HTTP mux pattern syntax with `http.ServeMux()`. The key routes are:\n- **`GET /runs`** — Primary route for the runs list view that supports the `?project=` query parameter\n- **`GET /projects/{name}/runs`** — Project-specific runs route that redirects to `/runs?project=<dir>`\n- **`GET /api/runs`** — JSON API that also supports `?project=` filtering\n\n### 2. **Query Parameter Handling in HTTP Handlers**\n\n#### **Handler: `handleRunsList` (lines 255-309)**\nThis is the main HTML view handler:\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) handleRunsList(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    projectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")  // Line 256\n    \n    if projectFilter != \"\" {\n        runs, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n    } else {\n        runs, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n    }\n    \n    // Passes to template as:\n    \"ProjectFilter\": projectFilter,  // Line 301\n}\n```\n\n#### **Handler: `handleAPIRuns` (lines 622-644)**\nThis is the JSON API handler:\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIRuns(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    projectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")  // Line 623\n    \n    if projectFilter != \"\" {\n        runs, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n    } else {\n        runs, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n    }\n    // Returns JSON array with grouped runs\n}\n```\n\n#### **Handler: `handleProjectRuns` (lines 311-318)**\nThis redirects to the query parameter version:\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) handleProjectRuns(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    dir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n    if !ok {\n        return\n    }\n    http.Redirect(w, r, \"/runs?project=\"+url.QueryEscape(dir), http.StatusFound)\n}\n```\n\n**Key Point:** The `project` query parameter expects a **project directory path** (e.g., `/home/user/myproject`), not a label. This is passed directly to `ListRunsByProject()` in the store.\n\n### 3. **Templates Generating Links**\n\n#### **File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (lines 64, 92)\n\n**Client-side JavaScript:**\n```javascript\nfunction filterByProject(dir) {\n    if (dir) {\n        window.location.href = '/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(dir);  // Line 64\n    } else {\n        window.location.href = '/runs';\n    }\n}\n\nfunction poll() {\n    var url = '/api/runs';\n    if (currentProject) {\n        url += '?project=' + encodeURIComponent(currentProject);  // Line 92\n    }\n    fetch(url)  // Polling endpoint every 3 seconds\n}\n```\n\n**HTML Dropdown (lines 4-11):**\n```html\n<select id=\"project-select\" onchange=\"filterByProject(this.value)\">\n    <option value=\"\">All projects</option>\n    {{range .Projects}}\n    <option value=\"{{.Dir}}\"{{if eq .Dir $.ProjectFilter}} selected{{end}}>\n        {{.Label}}...\n    </option>\n    {{end}}\n</select>\n```\n\nThe select dropdown value is the **project directory path** (`.Dir`), which gets passed to `filterByProject()`.\n\n#### **File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` (line 27)\n\nLinks to the project detail page:\n```html\n<a href=\"/projects/{{.Label}}/runs\" class=\"btn btn-secondary\">View Runs</a>\n```\n\nThis uses the project **label** (short name), which is then handled by `handleProjectRuns` and redirected to `/runs?project=<dir>`.\n\n### 4. **Data Flow and Structures**\n\n**In Handler Data Context:**\n- Template receives: `ProjectFilter` (raw directory path from query param)\n- Template receives: `Projects` (array of `projectEntry` with Dir/Label pairs)\n- Template receives: `ProjectLabels` (map of Dir → Label for display)\n\n**API Response Structure** (`apiRun` struct, lines 442-457):\n```go\ntype apiRun struct {\n    ID           string\n    ProjectDir   string     // Full directory path\n    ProjectLabel string     // Short display label\n    // ... other fields\n}\n```\n\n**Grouped Entry Structure** (`apiGroupedEntry`, lines 495-502):\n```go\ntype apiGroupedEntry struct {\n    TaskHeader bool\n    TaskID     string\n    TaskStatus string\n    IsParent   bool\n    IsChild    bool\n    Run        *apiRun\n}\n```\n\n### 5. **Project Label Resolution**\n\n**Function:** `projectLabels()` (lines 1777-1801)\n\nThis function builds a mapping from full directory paths to short labels:\n- Base case: `/home/user/myproject` → `myproject`\n- Conflict resolution: `/home/user/bar` and `/home/foo/bar` → `user/bar` and `foo/bar`\n\n**Note:** The resolution happens on the server side. The `project` query parameter uses **full directory paths**, while the UI displays and generates links using **project labels**. The redirect in `handleProjectRuns` converts the label-based URL to a directory path.\n\n### 6. **Test Coverage**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`\n\nKey test cases:\n- Lines 414-421: `TestRunsList_ProjectFilter` — Verifies project filtering works\n- Lines 437-466: `TestAPIRuns_ProjectFilter` — Tests API filtering with `?project=` parameter\n- Lines 424-435: `TestRunsList_ProjectColumn` — Verifies project display in runs table\n\n### 7. **Design Documentation**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`\n\nThe design doc indicates:\n- Line 31: Project cards should link to `/projects/{name}` (using project label)\n- Line 31: Project detail pages should include a \"View all runs\" link to the filtered runs list\n- Line 147: The project detail page loads workflows via `/api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n\n---\n\n## Complete URL Pattern Reference\n\n| Route | Method | Parameter | Handler | Purpose |\n|-------|--------|-----------|---------|---------|\n| `/runs` | GET | `?project=<dir>` | `handleRunsList` | Filtered runs list (HTML) |\n| `/api/runs` | GET | `?project=<dir>` | `handleAPIRuns` | Filtered runs list (JSON) |\n| `/projects/{name}/runs` | GET | None (name is label) | `handleProjectRuns` | Redirect to `/runs?project=<dir>` |\n| `/projects/{name}` | GET | None (name is label) | `handleProjectDetail` | Project detail page |\n| `/api/projects` | GET | None | `handleAPIProjects` | List all projects (JSON) |\n\n---\n\n## Files Containing URL Pattern References\n\n1. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** (Main handler logic)\n   - Route registration: lines 146-165\n   - Query parameter extraction: lines 256, 623\n   - Project runs redirect: lines 311-318\n   - Project label mapping: lines 1777-1801\n\n2. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`** (Template with JavaScript)\n   - Filter dropdown: lines 4-11\n   - JavaScript filter function: lines 62-68\n   - API polling with project filter: lines 90-94\n\n3. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html`** (Project cards)\n   - View Runs link: line 27\n\n4. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`** (Project page)\n   - View all runs link: line 8\n\n5. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`** (Test cases)\n   - Project filtering tests: lines 414-421, 437-466"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: 